A person shall not be appointed as Prosecutor General unless he is a citizen of Pakistan, and is not less than forty five years of age, and meets one of the following conditions:

- He has, for a period of, or for the periods aggregating, not less than ten years, been an Advocate of the High Court; 
- He has, for a period of not less than five years, performed functions of an Additional Prosecutor General and is enrolled as an Advocate of High Court; 
